# Day 3 — SimpleBank Contract

## What I Built
- SimpleBank — deposit, getBalance, withdraw

## What I Learned
- `payable` keyword lets a function receive ETH
- `msg.value` = amount of ETH sent with transaction
- `require()` = security check before executing logic
- `+=` adds to existing value, `-=` deducts from it
- `payable(msg.sender).transfer(amount)` sends ETH out
- Checks-Effects-Interactions pattern — update state BEFORE sending ETH

## Security Insight
- Reentrancy attack: if you send ETH before updating balance, attacker can call withdraw repeatedly and drain the contract

